node_modules/
.vite/
public/
# dist/ is the Vite build output. We don't commit minified assets
# (noisy review diffs, big repo). The //go:embed all:dist directive
# in embed.go needs *something* in dist/ at compile time, so .gitkeep
# stays tracked as a sentinel. On fresh clones with no Vite build,
# the Go server detects the empty embed and serves a stub HTML
# pointing at `go generate ./...`.
dist/*
!dist/.gitkeep
